D Note that here we don't allow Flash to create sinks
D or for sinks to accrete. We will create "sinks" which
D will represent MS stars without accretion, but it still
D allows us to use all the bridging stuff I wrote for
D sink particles already. - JW

PPDEFINE SINKS_AND_STARS

REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMapping/meshWeighting/MapToMesh
REQUIRES flashUtilities/sorting/quicksort
REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMain/active/massive

D Whether this sink is external to the simulation or formed in-situ.
D For including star particles from other simulations in Torch.
PARTICLEPROP EXTR REAL

D Mean gas sound speed around a sink.
PARTICLEPROP CSGM REAL

D This holds the gas velocity mean and gas
D velocity variance in each direction around
D a given sink particle.

D Mean
PARTICLEPROP VXGM REAL
PARTICLEPROP VYGM REAL
PARTICLEPROP VZGM REAL
D Variance
PARTICLEPROP VXGV REAL
PARTICLEPROP VYGV REAL
PARTICLEPROP VZGV REAL

D Here's a variable that holds the amount of time
D passed since a star was formed in this cell.

PARTICLETYPE ACTIVE INITMETHOD custom MAPMETHOD weighted ADVMETHOD PT_ADVMETH_NONE

D sfe            Local star formation efficiency (usually around 20-30%,
D                see Krumholz, Dekel and McKee 2011)

PARAMETER sfe                   REAL   0.3

D Injection radius for winds, or if no winds, refinement radius for
D blocks around active/massive particles.
D ref_radius REAL -1.0
PARAMETER ref_radius            REAL   -1.0
